Immediate past Minister of State for Agriculture, Senator Heineken Lokpobiri, has formally declared his intention to contest the November 16 governorship election in Bayelsa State on the platform of All Progressives Congress (APC). He made his intention known yesterday when he consulted the state leadership of APC at the party’s secretariat along Yebagoa-Mbiama road in the state capital. He told the party leadership that he is ready to lead APC to the Creek Haven, so that he can build economy beyond oil for the state. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE Lokpobiri said: “I’m here to formally inform my political family about my intention to run for the governorship of Bayelsa State under the APC platform. I have the support base to win the election come November 16. “My plea to the leadership of our party is to ensure that it remains united in order to form a formidable front to win this election, because if the party in unity, we will surely win the governorship election. “I’m coming to give direction to Bayelsa State, develop the state and build economy beyond oil”. Speaking, chairman of the APC in the state, Jothan Amos, said the primary election will be free and fair, urging all aspirants to carry out their consultations peacefully.  Ex minister, Lokpobiri declares for Bayelsa governorship Bayelsa: Suspense, anxiety as aspirants scramble for APC gov’ship ticket Aganaba joins Bayelsa gov’ship race Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin